  This kit interoperates with VisionOS-SimHands but does NOT include its source code:

  - `engine/simhands_bridge.mm` and `tools/simhands_canned_sender.swift` are original works —
    an independent ObjC++ / Swift re-implementation of the SimHands MultipeerConnectivity wire
    protocol (serviceType "Bonjour", the 21-landmark `{landmarks, handednesses}` JSON shape, and
    the MediaPipe left/right handedness swap). They speak the same protocol so SimHands' own macOS
    helper — or this kit's canned sender — can feed them.
  - To get REAL webcam hands you run SimHands' own macOS helper (Apache-2.0) unmodified. It is not
    redistributed here; clone it from the link above.

  Grateful credit to Ben Harraway for VisionOS-SimHands, which pioneered streaming MediaPipe webcam
  hands into the visionOS Simulator and defined the protocol this kit's engine bridge consumes.
